{
  "texts": [
    "In the pilot study conducted with the participation of 32 students, it was reported that they did not encounter any problems understanding the meaning of all the scale items.",
    "Additionally, the Cronbach Alpha value of the scale was calculated as 0.90.",
    "As part of the test-retest analysis conducted to assess the consistency and reliability of the scale over time, the Pearson correlation coefficient was found to be 0.82 (p < 0.001).",
    "The ICC value for the Single Measures model was determined to be 0.785 (95% CI [0.697, 0.849]), and for the Average Measures model, the ICC value was 0.897 (95% CI [0.822, 0.919]).",
    "In both cases, the p-value was found to be < 0.001, indicating that the obtained ICC values are statistically significant."
  ]
}